# NAME
. whoami(1) - print effective user ID

# SYNOPSIS
$ whoami [OPTION]...

# DESCRIPTION
. Print the user name associated with the current effective user ID.
  Equivalent to `` `id -un` ``.

# EXAMPLES
. Show current user:
$ whoami

# SEE ALSO
. {id(1)}, {logname(1)}, {who(1)}, {getuid(2)}
